Class Subspace_Analysis

  • java.lang.Object
    • jed.Subspace_Analysis

  • public class Subspace_Analysis
extends java.lang.Object
    JED class Subspace_Analysis: Core class for performing comparative subspace analysis. Note: The expected input is 2 matrices of eigenvectors representing 2 equidimensional subspaces from a vector space. If you are not sure if you are working with orthonormal bases (subsets of an eigenspace), there is a test_Orthogonal method. Orthonormal bases are expected. This means that the number of rows and columns must be the same.       • Subspace_Analysis

        public Subspace_Analysis(Jama.Matrix basis1,
                         Jama.Matrix basis2)
        Constructor to initiate the subspace analysis of two sets of eigenvectors. The sets of eigenvectors are equidimensional bases for subspaces of the eigenspaces of the trajectories.
        Parameters:
        basis1 - The first set of eigenvectors.
        basis2 - The second set of eigenvectors.
